00:00:12,245 --> 00:00:17,280
 and if we take Z raised to the power phi of N, which is P minus one,

6
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:23,390
 Q minus one, we get back one_mod_N, which is P_times_Q.

7
00:00:23,390 --> 00:00:28,220
 This fact here, is going to be the basis for the RSA algorithm.

8
00:00:28,220 --> 00:00:31,865
 We're going to generate a pair of prime numbers, P and Q.

9
